rajawali.scenegraph

Interface IGraphNode

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    A_nAABBTree, Octree

    public interface IGraphNode
    Generic interface allowing for the incorporation of scene graphs to the rendering pipeline of Rajawali. To be a member of scene graphs which implement this interface, an object must inherit from ATransformable3D.
    Author:
    Jared Woolston (jwoolston@tenkiv.com)

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  IGraphNode.GRAPH_TYPE
      This enum defines the different scene graphs which RajawaliScene can use.

    • Method Detail

      • addObject

        void addObject(IGraphNodeMember object)
        Adds an object to the scene graph. Implementations do not need to support online adjustment of the scene graph, and should clearly document what their add behavior is.
        Parameters:
        object - BaseObject3D to be added to the graph.

      • addObjects

        void addObjects(java.util.Collection<IGraphNodeMember> objects)
        Adds a collection of objects to the scene graph. Implementations do not need to support online adustment of the scene graph, and should clearly document what their add behavior is.
        Parameters:
        objects - Collection of IGraphNodeMember objects to add.

      • removeObject

        void removeObject(IGraphNodeMember object)
        Removes an object from the scene graph. Implementations do not need to support online adjustment of the scene graph, and should clearly document what their removal behavior is.
        Parameters:
        object - BaseObject3D to be removed from the graph.

      • removeObjects

        void removeObjects(java.util.Collection<IGraphNodeMember> objects)
        Removes a collection of objects from the scene graph. Implementations do not need to support online adjustment of the scene graph, and should clearly document what thier removal behavior is.
        Parameters:
        objects - Collection of IGraphNodeMember objects to remove.

      • updateObject

        void updateObject(IGraphNodeMember object)
        This should be called whenever an object has moved in the scene. Implementations should determine its new position in the graph.
        Parameters:
        object - BaseObject3D to re-examine.

      • addChildrenRecursively

        void addChildrenRecursively(boolean recursive)
        Set the child addition behavior. Implementations are expected to document their default behavior.
        Parameters:
        recursive - boolean Should the children be added recursively.

      • removeChildrenRecursively

        void removeChildrenRecursively(boolean recursive)
        Set the child removal behavior. Implementations are expected to document their default behavior.
        Parameters:
        recursive - boolean Should the children be removed recursively.

      • rebuild

        void rebuild()
        Can be called to force a reconstruction of the scene graph with all added children. This is useful if the scene graph does not support online modification.

      • clear

        void clear()
        Can be called to remove all objects from the scene graph.

      • cullFromBoundingVolume

        void cullFromBoundingVolume(IBoundingVolume volume)
        Called to cause the scene graph to determine which objects are contained (even partially) by the provided volume. How this is done is left to the implementation.
        Parameters:
        volume - IBoundingVolume to test visibility against.

      • displayGraph

        void displayGraph(Camera camera,
                Matrix4 vpMatrix,
                Matrix4 projMatrix,
                Matrix4 vMatrix)

        Parameters:
        display - boolean indicating if the graph is to be displayed.

      • getObjectCount

        int getObjectCount()
        Retrieve the number of objects this node is aware of. This count should be recursive, meaning each node should ask its children for a count and return the sum of that count.
        Returns:
        int containing the object count.
